###############################################################################
                 COMPLEX HILBERT SPACE EXPLORER (DEPRECATED)
###############################################################################

  This part contains the definitions and theorems used by the Hilbert
  Space Explorer ~ http://us.metamath.org/mpeuni/mmhil.html .  Because it
  axiomatizes a single complex Hilbert space whose existence is assumed,
  its usefulness is limited.  For example, it cannot work with real or
  quaternion Hilbert spaces and it cannot study relationships between two
  Hilbert spaces.  More information can be found on the Hilbert Space
  Explorer page.  Future development should work with general Hilbert
  spaces as defined by ~ df-hil .

$)

